    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ærǧæ" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>ærǧæ</orth></form>
                <usg><lang/></usg>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>глина</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>clay</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ил</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>silt</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re xml:lang="os-x-iron">
                    <lang/>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>ælyg</orth></form>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>dænttæ… fælmæn zænxæ raxwæruncæ; don lasuj ærǧæ æma zmesæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>реки размывают мягкую землю; река уносит глину и песок</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>rivers erode soft soil; the river takes clay and sand away</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>III
                            59</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*gri-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w>*graya-</w>
                        <gloss><q>глина</q></gloss></mentioned> с обычной метатезой %igr%i → %irǧ%i
                    и появлением протетического гласного %iæ-%i; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>grīha-</w>
                        <gloss><q>глина</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*ɣrīk(ɣryk)</w>
                        <gloss><q>глина</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘ил’, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>ɣrik</w>
                        <gloss><q>пыль</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>ɣərəy</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/>
                        <w>xrik</w></mentioned>. Корень *%igli%i-, *%iglei%i- со значением ‘вязкое,
                    липкое вещество’ является общеиндоевропейским; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>глина</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>γλίνη</w>
                        <gloss><q>клей</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                            ><w>γλοιός</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>glis</w>
                        <gloss><q>липкая, вязкая почва</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="la"><w>glūs</w>
                        <gloss><q>клей</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>Klei</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/>
                        <w>clay</w>
                        <gloss><q>глина</q></gloss></mentioned> и др. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/>
                        <w>ælyg</w>
                        <gloss><q>глина</q></gloss></mentioned>, несмотря на значительное звуковое
                    отличие от %iærǧæ%i, можно возводить к тому же корню; см. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ælyg"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"
                            /><biblScope>6</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*gri-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w>*graya-</w>
                        <gloss><q>clay</q></gloss></mentioned> with the regular transposition %igr%i
                    → %irǧ%i and the appearance of the prothetic vowel %iæ-%i; compare <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>grīha-</w>
                        <gloss><q>clay</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*ɣrīk(ɣryk)</w>
                        <gloss><q>clay</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘silt’, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>ɣrik</w>
                        <gloss><q>dust</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>ɣərəy</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/>
                        <w>xrik</w></mentioned>. The root *%igli%i-, *%iglei%i- with the meaning
                    ‘viscous, sticky substance’ is a common Indo-European root; compare <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>glina</w>
                        <gloss><q>clay</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>γλίνη</w>
                        <gloss><q>glue</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                            ><w>γλοιός</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>glis</w>
                        <gloss><q>sticky, swampy soil</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="la"><w>glūs</w>
                        <gloss><q>glue</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>Klei</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/>
                        <w>clay</w></mentioned> and so on. One may trace <mentioned
                        xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/>
                        <w>ælyg</w>
                        <gloss><q>clay</q></gloss></mentioned>, back to the same root regardless
                    significant sound difference from %iærǧæ%i, see <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ælyg"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"
                            /><biblScope>6</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
